  "response": "The classification of machine-made eggs as vegetarian or non-vegetarian depends on their composition and production process.\n\nTraditional eggs are considered non-vegetarian because they are animal products. However, machine-made or lab-grown eggs can vary:\n\nIf the machine-made egg is entirely plant-based, using ingredients like mung bean protein, algae, or other plant sources, it is considered vegetarian (or even vegan).\n\nIf the machine-made egg involves animal-derived ingredients (e.g., animal cells or proteins), it would be considered non-vegetarian.\n\nSo, whether machine-made eggs are vegetarian or not depends on their ingredients and the production method. Always check the label or manufacturer's information to be sure.",
